message.content: The most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as the paper deals with natural language processing and semantic representation of questions. Other likely sub-categories could be "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) as the paper discusses improving retrieval of similar questions, "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper uses neural network architectures for modeling, "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as the paper involves training models on limited annotations, and "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper deals with designing a methodology for finding semantically related questions.
